div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
The People of the United States of America, to the Cheif Sheriff Police of said City of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of Lee Kee by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Lee Kee shall be called or charged, before the HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of the aforesaid Court at Seattle in the Court House of said City on the 1st day of June 1885, fortwith to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Lee Kee And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 1st day of June A.D. 1885
JAMES SEAVEY, Clerk. By James P Ludlow Deputy
